Vendored Tesseract.js OCR engine
================================

Used by `js/ops/textDetect.js` for the "Detect text" auto-redact feature in
the redact tool (see docs/plans/2026-05-22-ocr-redact-design.md for the full
design).

Files
-----

- tesseract.min.js                                  — main library, UMD bundle (~63 KB)
- worker.min.js                                     — web-worker harness    (~111 KB)
- core/tesseract-core-lstm.wasm                     — LSTM-only WASM, no SIMD
- core/tesseract-core-lstm.wasm.js                  — its loader
- core/tesseract-core-simd-lstm.wasm                — LSTM-only WASM with SIMD
- core/tesseract-core-simd-lstm.wasm.js             — its loader
- core/tesseract-core-relaxedsimd-lstm.wasm         — LSTM-only WASM with relaxed-SIMD
- core/tesseract-core-relaxedsimd-lstm.wasm.js      — its loader
- lang/eng.traineddata.gz                           — English LSTM model (~1.9 MB gzipped)

We DO NOT vendor the non-`-lstm` core variants — those bundle Tesseract's
legacy integer-only OCR code paths in addition to the LSTM model and run
~600 KB larger each. We never enter legacy mode (Tesseract 5+ uses LSTM by
default; we expose only that).

Runtime variant selection: Tesseract.js auto-detects WASM feature support
and picks the fastest of the three vendored variants. Modern Chrome /
Firefox / Safari get the `relaxedsimd` build; mid-range mobiles get `simd`;
ancient browsers fall back to the plain variant. All three are single-
threaded — no SharedArrayBuffer, no COOP/COEP requirement.

Source
------

`tesseract.min.js` + `worker.min.js`:
  https://www.npmjs.com/package/tesseract.js  (v7.0.0)
  Tarball: https://registry.npmjs.org/tesseract.js/-/tesseract.js-7.0.0.tgz

`core/*.wasm` + `core/*.wasm.js`:
  https://www.npmjs.com/package/tesseract.js-core  (v7.0.0)
  Tarball: https://registry.npmjs.org/tesseract.js-core/-/tesseract.js-core-7.0.0.tgz

`lang/eng.traineddata.gz`:
  Repo:   https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tessdata_fast
  Commit: 87416418657359cb625c412a48b6e1d6d41c29bd  (HEAD on 2024-08-01)
  File:   eng.traineddata  (uncompressed; we gzip locally during vendor)

License
-------

Apache-2.0 for all three:

- Tesseract.js (Naptha):     https://github.com/naptha/tesseract.js/blob/master/LICENSE
- tesseract.js-core:         https://github.com/naptha/tesseract.js-core/blob/master/LICENSE
- tessdata_fast (model):     https://github.com/tesseract-ocr/tessdata_fast (per-repo Apache-2.0)

